    <div class="hero">
      <h1>ACS Secure AWS Project</h1>
      <p>
        Built a secure, auditable AWS environment using network segmentation, least-privilege IAM, centralized logging,
        compliance rules (AWS Config), and cost controls (budgets/alarms). Evidence is captured below by domain.
      </p>

      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card span-6">
          <h2>Goal</h2>
          <p>Deploy a public web tier with a controlled admin access path, strong logging/audit trail, and governance controls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card span-6">
          <h2>Key Outcomes</h2>
          <p>Segregated subnets, restricted SSH via bastion, CloudTrail + Flow Logs to CloudWatch, Config rules for compliance, billing alarms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card span-12">
          <h2>What this demonstrates</h2>
          <p>
            Practical cloud security build skills: secure-by-design networking, access control, monitoring & logging,
            continuous compliance, and cost governance — with evidence artifacts to support each control.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTROLS OVERVIEW -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Controls implemented</h2>
      <p class="sub">Organised like a real security review: Network, IAM, Logging/Monitoring, Compliance/Governance, Cost Management.</p>

      <div class="controls">
        <div class="control">
          <h3>Network</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Public and private subnet segmentation</li>
            <li>Internet Gateway for public tier only</li>
            <li>Restricted SSH via bastion security group</li>
            <li>VPC Flow Logs enabled to CloudWatch Logs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="control">
          <h3>IAM</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Admin group and controlled user access</li>
            <li>MFA enabled for console access</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="control">
          <h3>Logging & Monitoring</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>CloudTrail enabled (audit trail)</li>
            <li>CloudWatch Logs receiving events</li>
            <li>Dashboard view for at-a-glance status</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="control">
          <h3>Compliance & Governance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>AWS Config rules enabled (continuous evaluation)</li>
            <li>Non-compliance visibility for remediation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="control">
          <h3>Cost Management</h3>
          <ul>
